observations.recommendation:
a. The Local Treasurer and the Local Accountant to submit to the LSB of the certified statement containing the following enumerated below, not later than July 15 of the current year as basis for the formulation of SEF budget.
I. Actual SEF income for the immediately preceding fiscal year;
II. Actual SEF income for the first two quarters of the current year;
III. The estimated SEF income for the last two quarters of the current year; and
IV. The annual estimates for the ensuing year.
b. The LSB shall furnish the Local Budget Officer, the Local Accountant, and the Local Treasurer a copy of the SEF Budget as basis for disbursement or certification of availability of funds and for recording purposes.

The Municipal Treasurer/Property Officer shall maintain stock ledger cards, property ;edger cards, WOABSLC and other subsidiary records and reconcile accounting and property records periodically;
The Inventory Committee shall conduct complete physical inventory of all property and reconcile results with accounting records and record any adjustments in the books;
The Municipal Accountant shall provide depreciation on all depreciable assets and ensure the reconciliation and update of the aforementioned dormant accounts; and
The Municipal Treasurer/Property officer should prepare the Inventory and Inspection Report of all identified unserviceable properties and facilitates their immediate disposal to prevent further deterioration and decrease in salvage values. The Municipal Accountant should effect the necessary adjustments in the PPE Account to reclassify the book value of unserviceable properties to Other Assets account pending disposal and close the corresponding Accumulated Depreciation.

Ensure that identified PPAs address emerging gender-related issues and concerns pursuant to PCW DILG DNM and NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2013-01;

Utilization of GAD Budget Should be in accordance with the DILG-approved GAD Plan and Budget; and

Submit monthly accomplishment report to our office.

